# Main.elm — EARLY

TEA bootstrap for the standalone LynRummy Elm game. Wires the
model, Msg, update, view, and subscriptions into
`Browser.element`. Post-extractions, Main.elm is thin: init,
update-dispatch, the MouseMove/Up decoders, subscriptions, and
the URL-path port.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Active churn but shrinking — replay
  machinery (FSM + spatial synthesis) moved to
  `Main/Replay/Time.elm` and `Main/Replay/Space.elm` on
  2026-04-21. Game-state transitions already live in
  `Main/Apply.elm`; rendering in `Main/View.elm`; pointer
  gesture machinery in `Main/Gesture.elm`; HTTP in
  `Main/Wire.elm`; types + initial model in `Main/State.elm`.

## Dispatch map

`update` dispatches on Msg. Most branches are one-liners that
delegate to a helper module; the remaining inline branches are
(a) tiny (MouseMove cursor bookkeeping, WingEntered/Left hover,
PopupOk) or (b) tightly coupled to multiple Model fields
(ClickCompleteTurn, CompleteTurnResponded, BoardRectReceived,
ClickHint).

| Msg | Handler |
|---|---|
| `MouseDownOnBoardCard` / `MouseDownOnHandCard` | `Main.Gesture.start*` |
| `MouseMove` | inline cursor + path bookkeeping |
| `MouseUp` | `Main.Gesture.handleMouseUp` |
| `WingEntered` / `WingLeft` | inline |
| `ActionSent` | inline no-op (fire-and-forget) |
| `SessionReceived` | inline — stash sid + pin URL |
| `ClickCompleteTurn` | inline — referee pre-check + sendCompleteTurn |
| `CompleteTurnResponded` | inline — `applyAction WA.CompleteTurn` + dealt-card diagnostic |
| `PopupOk` | inline — popup dismiss |
| `ClickInstantReplay` | `Main.Replay.Time.clickInstantReplay` |
| `ReplayFrame` | `Main.Replay.Time.replayFrame` |
| `ClickReplayPauseToggle` | `Main.Replay.Time.clickReplayPauseToggle` |
| `HandCardRectReceived` | `Main.Replay.Time.handCardRectReceived` |
| `BoardRectReceived` | inline — shared by live-drag AND replay |
| `ActionLogFetched` | inline — stash actions + gestures + baseline |
| `StateRefreshed` | inline — hydrate Model from server |
| `ClickHint` | inline — `Hint.buildSuggestions` + highlight |

`BoardRectReceived` stays inline because it has two consumers
in the same Msg: the active live-drag (drop-target math) and
the active replay (board-frame → viewport translation). Pulling
it into one of the two contexts would hide the shared update.

## "One log, source-agnostic" invariant

Every validated WireAction — local gesture, replay tick, or
(future) wire receive — flows through `applyAction` before
anything else touches the Model. "Capture the input, update the
data structure, re-draw the view."

## Subscriptions

- `Browser.Events.onMouseMove` / `onMouseUp` — subscribed only
  while `drag = Dragging _`.
- `Browser.Events.onAnimationFrame` → `ReplayFrame` — subscribed
  only while `replay = Just { paused = False }`. Drives both the
  drag-path interpolation and the beat phase.

## Port

- `setSessionPath : String -> Cmd msg` — writes the URL path
  to `/gopher/lynrummy-elm/play/<sid>` whenever a session id is
  known. Server-side rendering reads the path on reload and
  resumes the same game instead of dropping to the lobby.

## Replay architecture

The replay walker lives across two modules, split by concern:

- `Main/Replay/Time.elm` — FSM, clock-driven Msg handlers,
  inter-action beat durations. Owns the decision of "what
  phase am I in and when do I transition."
- `Main/Replay/Space.elm` — spatial synthesis: endpoints, path
  interpolation, drag-source resolution, DOM-measured board /
  hand rects. Owns the "where does the drag live in pixel
  space" question.

Space is pure; Time depends on Space; Main depends on both.
See the companion sidecars for detail.

### Rule for adding synthesis to new primitives

Any viewport coord the replay synthesizer consumes must come
from DOM measurement, not from a pinned constant. See
`Main/Replay/Space.claude` § "Rule for adding synthesis" for
the full rule and the 2026-04-21 "landing right, origin wrong"
incident that motivated it.

## Pointers

- Autonomy-core: `Game.Game` (`Game.elm`) — `GameState`
  record and `applyCompleteTurn` transition. Main embeds those
  fields; changes to game state go through Game's functions.
- Hosted at `index.html` in this dir; built into `elm.js` via
  `npx elm make src/Main.elm --output=elm.js` (runs
  automatically in `ops/start`).
- Served through Gopher at `http://localhost:9000/gopher/lynrummy-elm/`.
- Pinned geometry: `Game.BoardGeometry`,
  `Game.HandLayout`.

